# Project Structure Documentation

Document project structure in STRUCTURE.md.

<rule>
name: project_structure_events
description: Suggest updating STRUCTURE.md when structural changes occur

filters:
  # Trigger on file create/delete/move events
  - type: event
    pattern: "(?i)^(file_(create|delete|move))$"
  # Ignore VCS internals
  - type: path
    pattern: "^(?!\\.git/).+"

actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      A structural change was detected (file create, delete, or move).
      Review and update STRUCTURE.md if directory purposes or key locations changed.

criteria:
  required:
    - STRUCTURE.md exists in project root
    - Update STRUCTURE.md when directories are added/removed/moved
    - Keep key component locations current

metadata:
  priority: medium
  version: 1.2
</rule>

<rule>
name: project_structure_authoring
description: Provide authoring guidance when editing STRUCTURE.md or asking about structure

filters:
  - type: file
    pattern: "STRUCTURE\\.md$"
  - type: intent
    pattern: "(?i)\\b(structure|organization|layout|architecture)\\b"

actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      STRUCTURE.md should include:
      1. Project organization overview
      2. Key directories and purposes
      3. Important file locations
      4. Component dependencies
      5. Configuration file locations

      Update when adding directories, moving files, or changing structure.

criteria:
  required:
    - STRUCTURE.md exists in project root
    - File is up-to-date with current structure
    - All major components documented
    - Directory purposes explained
    - Key file locations listed

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.2
</rule>


